WEBVTT

00:00:47.672 --> 00:00:50.967
THE APARTMENT JOB

00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:53.845
Four billion?

00:00:55.597 --> 00:00:57.432
You pocketed four billion won?

00:00:58.016 --> 00:01:00.018
Our apartment complex only has 1,200 households,

00:01:00.602 --> 00:01:02.353
And I skimmed that much.

00:01:02.437 --> 00:01:03.271
But this place

00:01:03.855 --> 00:01:06.983
Has almost 10,000 households.

00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:09.861
Then how much do you think you can skim off?

00:01:10.612 --> 00:01:12.238
A billion? Two billion?

00:01:12.322 --> 00:01:14.741
That's pocket change!

00:01:15.325 --> 00:01:17.035
You could even skim off ten billion!

00:01:20.163 --> 00:01:22.457
I'm serious, Mr. Park!

00:01:23.208 --> 00:01:24.125
Ten billion?

00:01:24.209 --> 00:01:25.210
Yes.

00:01:31.382 --> 00:01:32.425
We can skim off

00:01:32.509 --> 00:01:33.885
Ten billion won

00:01:33.968 --> 00:01:35.553
From this apartment complex?

00:01:44.395 --> 00:01:45.438
Release him.

00:01:45.522 --> 00:01:47.190
What? Oh, okay.

00:01:47.273 --> 00:01:48.608
Hey, untie him.

00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:05.834
How do we skim off ten billion then?

00:02:07.710 --> 00:02:08.586
Well

00:02:10.255 --> 00:02:11.589
You have to become

00:02:13.466 --> 00:02:15.426
The president of the residents' association.

00:02:17.262 --> 00:02:18.346
The president?

00:02:18.429 --> 00:02:19.722
Me?

00:02:19.806 --> 00:02:20.890
Yes.

00:02:21.808 --> 00:02:23.101
Tie him up again.

00:02:23.184 --> 00:02:25.562
That's enough of your nonsense!

00:02:25.645 --> 00:02:27.856
Hey! Don't touch me!

00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:29.566
The grown-ups are talking,

00:02:29.649 --> 00:02:30.942
You little brat.

00:02:31.025 --> 00:02:32.861
Didn't you see him giving me my jacket?

00:02:33.444 --> 00:02:34.988
Mr. Park.

00:02:35.071 --> 00:02:36.990
Just hear me out, okay?

00:02:37.073 --> 00:02:39.492
The only people who have access

00:02:39.576 --> 00:02:40.535
To the repair reserve fund

00:02:40.618 --> 00:02:43.413
Are the facility manager and the president.

00:02:43.496 --> 00:02:45.206
If those two are in on it together,

00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:48.418
Draining an entire apartment complex would be a piece of cake.

00:02:48.501 --> 00:02:51.171
Let's just throw him off. We have no use for you now.

00:02:51.254 --> 00:02:52.589
Wait, stop!

00:02:53.590 --> 00:02:55.508
-Wait! Please! -Throw him off!

00:02:56.801 --> 00:03:00.471
Mr. Park, I saw the notice in the elevator on my way here.

00:03:00.555 --> 00:03:02.307
Your apartment complex

00:03:02.390 --> 00:03:05.310
Is having a building representative election.

00:03:05.393 --> 00:03:08.730
Become the building representative, then the president.

00:03:08.813 --> 00:03:11.941
Then you'll be able to pocket ten billion won!

00:03:12.442 --> 00:03:14.819
You're telling me to become a building representative?

00:03:14.903 --> 00:03:15.820
Yes.

00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:17.989
Hang him.

00:03:18.072 --> 00:03:19.490
-Hey, tie him up again. -All right.

00:03:19.574 --> 00:03:21.618
I'm sorry!

00:03:21.701 --> 00:03:23.494
I'm so sorry, Mr. Park.

00:03:23.578 --> 00:03:25.204
You're right.

00:03:25.788 --> 00:03:29.584
I didn't realize it would be humiliating for someone like you

00:03:29.667 --> 00:03:33.296
To be an apartment building representative.

00:03:33.379 --> 00:03:34.672
I'm sorry.

00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:36.215
I'm sorry, Mr. Park.

00:03:36.299 --> 00:03:38.927
I'm sorry I hurt your pride.

00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:40.428
But there's no other way.

00:03:40.511 --> 00:03:42.513
You have to be a building representative

00:03:43.181 --> 00:03:45.767
To qualify to run for president.

00:03:46.893 --> 00:03:49.312
Can anyone become the building rep?

00:03:49.395 --> 00:03:51.856
Anyone can do it!

00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:53.524
Just ask the residents here.

00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:55.693
No one even cares about the building rep.

00:03:55.777 --> 00:03:56.861
If you volunteer,

00:03:56.945 --> 00:03:58.988
You're pretty much guaranteed to get elected.

00:03:59.072 --> 00:04:01.407
I mean it.

00:04:01.991 --> 00:04:03.368
I'll get elected

00:04:04.702 --> 00:04:06.162
If I just volunteer?

00:04:06.246 --> 00:04:07.538
BUILDING REPRESENTATIVE ELECTION

00:04:07.622 --> 00:04:09.457
See? I told you.

00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:11.334
You're not seriously buying this, are you?

00:04:11.417 --> 00:04:12.418
It's ridiculous.

00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:16.798
Boss.

00:04:24.681 --> 00:04:26.266
The door is closing.

00:05:06.639 --> 00:05:07.640
With ten billion

00:05:08.766 --> 00:05:10.560
We can save Yong-man

00:05:10.643 --> 00:05:12.729
And make a fresh start.

00:05:13.313 --> 00:05:16.733
But even if you get lucky and become the representative,

00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:19.569
Would there really be ten billion here?

00:05:20.653 --> 00:05:23.614
If you really don't believe me, call them.

00:05:23.698 --> 00:05:24.907
Call who?

00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:26.617
The management office.

00:05:26.701 --> 00:05:30.163
Ask them how much the long-term repair reserve fund is.

00:05:30.246 --> 00:05:31.539
Long-term what?

00:05:31.622 --> 00:05:33.833
What kind of fund is that?

00:05:34.709 --> 00:05:35.543
Gosh.

00:05:35.626 --> 00:05:38.171
The long-term repair

00:05:38.254 --> 00:05:39.505
You dimwits.

00:05:39.589 --> 00:05:43.259
The apartment complex collects money from residents over a long period.

00:05:43.342 --> 00:05:44.510
"Long-term."

00:05:44.594 --> 00:05:47.680
If something's broken, you repair it.

00:05:47.764 --> 00:05:50.600
"Repair." Hence, "long-term repair reserve fund."

00:05:50.683 --> 00:05:54.604
Please call them and ask how much they have.

00:06:06.991 --> 00:06:08.117
Miss Kang!

00:06:09.410 --> 00:06:11.370
What time do you even come to work?

00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:13.498
You're here early, Yun-seo.

00:06:13.581 --> 00:06:15.875
I thought I'd be here first today.

00:06:19.504 --> 00:06:21.798
It's not even 9:00 yet. Should I answer?

00:06:21.881 --> 00:06:23.674
Yes, it could be something urgent.

00:06:25.760 --> 00:06:28.596
This is the management office. How may I help you?

00:06:28.679 --> 00:06:31.307
Hello. Good morning.

00:06:32.016 --> 00:06:33.017
I'm

00:06:33.601 --> 00:06:35.561
One of the residents.

00:06:35.645 --> 00:06:37.230
Well, I

00:06:37.313 --> 00:06:39.690
I wanted to ask you something.

00:06:40.191 --> 00:06:43.361
The repair reserve fund

00:06:45.238 --> 00:06:49.033
How much is in the long-term repair reserve fund?

00:06:50.493 --> 00:06:53.162
The long-term repair reserve fund?

00:06:53.246 --> 00:06:54.288
Well

00:06:54.872 --> 00:06:55.748
Just a moment, sir.

00:06:56.290 --> 00:06:58.668
Miss Kang, he's asking how much is in the repair reserve fund.

00:07:00.002 --> 00:07:00.962
Who is it?

00:07:01.045 --> 00:07:02.880
A resident. What should I tell him?

00:07:05.341 --> 00:07:07.135
Just tell him how much.

00:07:08.052 --> 00:07:09.137
Yes, sir.

00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:11.722
You want to know how much is in the fund?

00:07:11.806 --> 00:07:13.808
Just a moment.

00:07:14.976 --> 00:07:18.855
There's 17,857,420,000 won.

00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:22.650
Sir, as you probably know,

00:07:22.733 --> 00:07:25.445
The apartment complex will need repairs as it ages,

00:07:25.528 --> 00:07:27.530
So we collect fees in advance to save--

00:07:29.198 --> 00:07:30.032
Hello?

00:07:30.783 --> 00:07:31.868
Sir?

00:07:33.911 --> 00:07:35.580
-No way! -They really have ten billion?

00:07:35.663 --> 00:07:37.248
It's more than that. It's 17--

00:07:37.331 --> 00:07:39.750
It's 17,857,420,000 won.

00:07:39.834 --> 00:07:41.711
Hang on. They actually have it.

00:07:41.794 --> 00:07:42.795
I can't believe it.

00:07:42.879 --> 00:07:46.591
The facility manager here must've taken good care of the fund.

00:07:46.674 --> 00:07:48.342
It's more than I expected.

00:07:49.093 --> 00:07:50.219
Gosh, my knees.

00:07:59.729 --> 00:08:01.939
Hey, you're the youngest here, aren't you?

00:08:02.023 --> 00:08:04.775
Go and make some hot coffee for me.

00:08:07.570 --> 00:08:08.946
So, Mr. Park,

00:08:09.030 --> 00:08:10.656
Do you believe me now?

00:08:11.574 --> 00:08:13.576
Hey, let's actually do this.

00:08:13.659 --> 00:08:15.870
That 17,857,420,000 won.

00:08:16.454 --> 00:08:19.123
We're going to take it.

00:08:22.376 --> 00:08:23.836
THE APARTMENT JOB

00:08:27.507 --> 00:08:29.133
Try it like this, Seo-jun.

00:08:29.217 --> 00:08:30.051
Yes.

00:08:30.134 --> 00:08:31.177
Like that.

00:08:32.094 --> 00:08:32.970
You did great.

00:08:33.054 --> 00:08:34.430
You're doing great.

00:08:35.848 --> 00:08:37.141
SAPLING NAME: MIN-JUN'S TREE

00:08:37.225 --> 00:08:38.893
SAPLING NAME: RU-I

00:08:39.852 --> 00:08:41.437
I was so surprised.

00:08:41.521 --> 00:08:43.231
How did you come up with this idea?

00:08:43.314 --> 00:08:45.191
Now this is real education.

00:08:45.274 --> 00:08:46.692
Right?

00:08:46.776 --> 00:08:48.444
Donating to an arboretum

00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:52.573
And using the saplings they gave you to help teach the children about nature.

00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:53.950
It's amazing.

00:08:54.033 --> 00:08:55.701
You even donate to an arboretum?

00:08:55.785 --> 00:08:56.702
You're so thoughtful.

00:08:56.786 --> 00:08:58.246
-I know, right? -I admire that.

00:08:58.329 --> 00:09:00.581
I thought that planting saplings with the kids

00:09:00.665 --> 00:09:02.750
Would be good for their emotional development.

00:09:04.252 --> 00:09:05.336
It's nothing special.

00:09:05.419 --> 00:09:07.213
You're so cool.

00:09:08.339 --> 00:09:09.507
What is this?

00:09:10.091 --> 00:09:13.844
Who said you could plant stuff like this here?

00:09:15.596 --> 00:09:16.973
This is ridiculous.

00:09:17.056 --> 00:09:21.435
Don't you know how expensive our apartment complex is?

00:09:21.519 --> 00:09:24.814
They poured a fortune into the landscaping design.

00:09:24.897 --> 00:09:27.275
Who gave you permission to plant this crap here?

00:09:27.358 --> 00:09:28.192
What?

00:09:28.776 --> 00:09:31.320
What did you say? "Crap"?

00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:33.072
How can you say such a thing?

00:09:33.155 --> 00:09:34.657
Did I say anything wrong?

00:09:35.533 --> 00:09:38.369
Whose land is this? Is it yours?

00:09:38.452 --> 00:09:39.328
Excuse me.

00:09:39.412 --> 00:09:42.039
We can plant stuff here if we're residents.

00:09:42.123 --> 00:09:43.416
I'm a resident too.

00:09:43.499 --> 00:09:45.876
There are loads of residents here.

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.212
You should get their permission.

00:09:48.296 --> 00:09:50.298
It's not like we did something bad.

00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:51.591
It's for the kids' education.

00:09:51.674 --> 00:09:52.883
Mothers,

00:09:52.967 --> 00:09:54.844
Let me tell you something. Listen up.

00:09:54.927 --> 00:09:57.221
I get your enthusiasm, but this tacky parenting.

00:09:57.305 --> 00:09:58.973
-Goodness. -Tacky?

00:09:59.056 --> 00:10:00.850
Just do it in your own homes!

00:10:01.851 --> 00:10:04.895
We're teaching them about nature

00:10:04.979 --> 00:10:06.856
And how to respect life.

00:10:06.939 --> 00:10:08.316
You call that tacky?

00:10:08.399 --> 00:10:09.984
You actually have a point.

00:10:10.067 --> 00:10:12.278
Fine, but before you teach them that,

00:10:12.361 --> 00:10:14.405
Why don't you teach them

00:10:14.488 --> 00:10:18.576
About shared communities and respecting your neighbors first?

00:10:18.659 --> 00:10:20.494
"Nature"? You've got to be kidding me.

00:10:20.578 --> 00:10:24.457
Then should I try planting lettuce, peppers, and cabbage

00:10:24.540 --> 00:10:25.791
All over the place?

00:10:25.875 --> 00:10:26.876
That's different.

00:10:26.959 --> 00:10:29.670
What's different? It's the same!

00:10:29.754 --> 00:10:31.547
Hurry up and pull these out!

00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:32.506
What if we won't?

00:10:33.215 --> 00:10:34.675
-You won't? -No.

00:10:34.759 --> 00:10:35.593
No!

00:10:39.263 --> 00:10:40.723
All right, then.

00:10:43.392 --> 00:10:44.435
Hey!

00:10:46.312 --> 00:10:47.688
I can't believe this!

00:10:48.564 --> 00:10:49.565
What's she doing?

00:10:49.649 --> 00:10:50.816
She must be crazy!

00:10:50.900 --> 00:10:52.652
-What are you doing? -Stop it!

00:10:53.319 --> 00:10:54.862
She really pisses me off.

00:10:54.945 --> 00:10:56.238
I can't believe her.

00:10:56.322 --> 00:10:57.406
She's so stuck up.

00:10:57.490 --> 00:10:59.867
Did you hear her going on about rules?

00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:01.744
She was so annoying.

00:11:01.827 --> 00:11:03.496
Who even is she?

00:11:03.579 --> 00:11:05.081
It's obvious, isn't it?

00:11:05.164 --> 00:11:07.667
She's just an ignorant person.

00:11:07.750 --> 00:11:09.293
Actually,

00:11:09.377 --> 00:11:11.629
I overheard the guards talking about her.

00:11:11.712 --> 00:11:13.464
They said she's a former beauty queen.

00:11:13.547 --> 00:11:15.841
No way. Miss Korea?

00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:17.385
A beauty queen? That's insane.

00:11:17.468 --> 00:11:20.054
I bet she won a lunatic contest, not a beauty pageant.

00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:22.723
That's crazy.

00:11:22.807 --> 00:11:24.809
I'm not sure about the details,

00:11:24.892 --> 00:11:29.271
But I heard that there are photos of her from the beauty pageant

00:11:29.355 --> 00:11:31.148
Plastered all over her walls.

00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:33.984
They must be fake photos. That can't be true.

00:11:34.068 --> 00:11:35.861
In any case,

00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:36.946
I think we need someone

00:11:37.029 --> 00:11:40.199
To represent us young mothers in our apartment complex.

00:11:41.075 --> 00:11:43.911
There are over 3000 preschoolers here,

00:11:43.994 --> 00:11:46.914
But there's no one to speak for all those mothers.

00:11:46.997 --> 00:11:49.375
You have a great point.

00:11:49.458 --> 00:11:52.002
Someone who can understand us and take our side

00:11:52.086 --> 00:11:54.505
Should be president of the residents' association

00:11:54.588 --> 00:11:55.673
For us to have influence.

00:11:55.756 --> 00:11:58.134
-You're right. -They're electing the building reps.

00:11:58.217 --> 00:12:00.678
Won't they pick the president from among them?

00:12:00.761 --> 00:12:02.221
-Yes. -I think so.

00:12:03.389 --> 00:12:04.640
You know,

00:12:04.723 --> 00:12:06.308
You should try running.

00:12:07.143 --> 00:12:08.436
We'll give you our full support.

00:12:10.563 --> 00:12:11.397
Me?

00:12:11.981 --> 00:12:14.358
You're thoughtful and socially conscious.

00:12:14.442 --> 00:12:16.277
You should be a voice for us mothers.

00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:19.071
If you run this time, we'll back you up no matter what.

00:12:19.155 --> 00:12:21.240
Yes, you can do it.

00:12:22.324 --> 00:12:23.576
How would I

00:12:26.495 --> 00:12:28.956
But who's the current president?

00:12:32.334 --> 00:12:33.294
I don't know.

00:12:34.712 --> 00:12:35.629
I have no idea.

00:12:38.841 --> 00:12:39.884
Yes?

00:12:39.967 --> 00:12:41.177
PRESIDENT SEO GANG-WON

00:12:47.641 --> 00:12:49.310
Is everything all right?

00:12:51.020 --> 00:12:53.105
I

00:12:57.318 --> 00:12:58.235
Sir.

00:12:58.319 --> 00:13:01.030
"I"

00:13:01.113 --> 00:13:04.283
Whenever you hesitate like that,

00:13:04.366 --> 00:13:06.911
It turns out to be something troublesome.

00:13:06.994 --> 00:13:08.037
You're scaring me.

00:13:09.288 --> 00:13:10.289
Well,

00:13:10.372 --> 00:13:12.291
Some young mothers caused a scene

00:13:12.374 --> 00:13:15.503
Over planting saplings in a flower bed within the complex.

00:13:16.086 --> 00:13:17.379
Is that so?

00:13:17.463 --> 00:13:20.799
I wrapped up the issue by saying we'd discuss it during a meeting, but--

00:13:20.883 --> 00:13:25.346
I told you several times that it'll die down if we stay quiet.

00:13:25.429 --> 00:13:28.599
Don't cause a bigger problem by getting involved,

00:13:28.682 --> 00:13:30.017
And just leave it be.

00:13:30.100 --> 00:13:31.852
Don't do anything.

00:13:31.936 --> 00:13:34.897
The trick to staying on as a facility manager for years

00:13:34.980 --> 00:13:38.484
Is to just laugh it off and do nothing

00:13:39.401 --> 00:13:41.529
No matter what the residents say.

00:13:42.780 --> 00:13:43.614
Right.

00:13:47.201 --> 00:13:50.663
Is there another "I" to say to me?

00:13:50.746 --> 00:13:52.248
Why aren't you leaving?

00:13:53.666 --> 00:13:57.836
Ha-jeong is saying she'll stop doing that job.

00:14:09.723 --> 00:14:13.018
An acquaintance of mine gave this tea to me.

00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:16.480
The scent is quite nice.

00:14:18.107 --> 00:14:22.111
I heard your sister became a lawyer.

00:14:22.194 --> 00:14:23.070
Congratulations.

00:14:23.153 --> 00:14:25.364
She must be quite amazing.

00:14:26.240 --> 00:14:27.491
Thank you.

00:14:29.702 --> 00:14:32.288
You heard from Mr. Choi, right?

00:14:33.622 --> 00:14:34.748
I can't do

00:14:35.416 --> 00:14:36.667
That job anymore.

00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:39.378
But

00:14:39.461 --> 00:14:41.547
If your sister finds out

00:14:41.630 --> 00:14:46.093
What kind of money you've been supporting her studies with,

00:14:46.176 --> 00:14:48.304
Wouldn't she be pretty disappointed in you?

00:14:48.387 --> 00:14:50.848
I just think that your sister

00:14:50.931 --> 00:14:54.351
Would be better off not knowing about what you've been doing.

00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:59.690
But I really can't do it any longer.

00:15:00.774 --> 00:15:02.359
I won't tell anyone about it.

00:15:02.943 --> 00:15:04.737
I promise to keep my mouth shut.

00:15:07.615 --> 00:15:09.825
If you feel uneasy with me here,

00:15:09.909 --> 00:15:12.661
I'll resign from the management office.

00:15:12.745 --> 00:15:14.038
Just let me quit.

00:15:17.374 --> 00:15:18.500
Did you think that

00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:22.588
If you said you'd back out on your own like this,

00:15:22.671 --> 00:15:24.757
I'd just say, "Sure, do as you please"?

00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:28.052
Do you really think I'd just let you leave?

00:15:34.391 --> 00:15:36.518
I'm just kidding.

00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:40.898
It was a joke.

00:15:40.981 --> 00:15:43.275
This tastes nice. Go on.

00:15:47.363 --> 00:15:49.698
"A facility manager in an apartment complex

00:15:49.782 --> 00:15:51.992
With 1200 households has been suspected

00:15:52.076 --> 00:15:55.204
Of embezzling four billion won over five years by falsifying accounts.

00:15:55.287 --> 00:15:58.666
The police are currently tracking his whereabouts." So what?

00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:02.503
That guy the article's talking about

00:16:02.586 --> 00:16:03.879
Is me.

00:16:03.963 --> 00:16:06.382
Wow, you're a total scumbag.

00:16:06.465 --> 00:16:07.716
Hang on.

00:16:07.800 --> 00:16:10.135
The complex residents aren't doing anything

00:16:10.219 --> 00:16:12.012
Even after losing all that money?

00:16:12.680 --> 00:16:14.014
Well, technically speaking,

00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:17.142
It's the same as each household losing about 30,000 won a month.

00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:21.063
Who would waste their time and energy to get that tiny sum back?

00:16:21.146 --> 00:16:23.107
No one in Korea would do that.

00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:25.192
Everyone's busy with their own lives.

00:16:25.275 --> 00:16:28.237
It's better for them to just work and earn money in that time.

00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:30.531
They don't even care about it.

00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:36.620
That's why we can skim off the money?

00:16:36.704 --> 00:16:38.330
Because they don't care?

00:16:40.457 --> 00:16:43.544
WHAT IS THE LONG-TERM REPAIR RESERVE FUND?

00:16:45.879 --> 00:16:48.257
Before we begin, raise your hand

00:16:48.340 --> 00:16:51.593
If you've ever lived in an apartment complex before.

00:16:53.303 --> 00:16:54.471
Put them down.

00:16:54.555 --> 00:16:56.390
Then while you were living there,

00:16:56.473 --> 00:17:01.270
Has anyone ever been curious about what the long-term repair reserve fund is?

00:17:02.896 --> 00:17:04.773
Right? I understand.

00:17:04.857 --> 00:17:08.777
Loads of people have no idea what this is, even if they live in an apartment.

00:17:08.861 --> 00:17:10.279
Just start explaining.

00:17:11.655 --> 00:17:12.781
To put it simply

00:17:13.365 --> 00:17:16.785
It's a fund collected in advance for long-term repairs

00:17:16.869 --> 00:17:18.871
For the apartment complex.

00:17:18.954 --> 00:17:20.330
If residents are asked to pay

00:17:20.414 --> 00:17:22.583
For the fees all at once later, they'll be pissed.

00:17:22.666 --> 00:17:24.835
As people get older,

00:17:24.918 --> 00:17:27.254
Their bodies start hurting here and there.

00:17:27.337 --> 00:17:29.506
It's the same for apartment buildings.

00:17:29.590 --> 00:17:32.551
So this fund is saved for such moments!

00:17:32.634 --> 00:17:37.014
That's what the long-term repair reserve fund is.

00:17:37.097 --> 00:17:40.100
Mr. Park, how much did you pay into the fund this month?

00:17:41.852 --> 00:17:43.270
29,360 won.

00:17:43.353 --> 00:17:46.482
Let's round it down to 29,000 won.

00:17:46.565 --> 00:17:48.067
And how many households?

00:17:48.150 --> 00:17:49.401
There are 9800 households.

00:17:49.485 --> 00:17:51.862
9,800 households.

00:17:51.945 --> 00:17:53.739
-Multiply it and-- -It's 284.2 million.

00:17:56.366 --> 00:17:57.826
Right.

00:17:57.910 --> 00:18:00.913
That amount has been piling up each month,

00:18:00.996 --> 00:18:04.500
And now, there's about 17.85 billion won

00:18:04.583 --> 00:18:05.918
Sitting in that fund!

00:18:06.794 --> 00:18:08.420
So the people managing the fund

00:18:08.504 --> 00:18:10.631
Are the president and facility manager?

00:18:10.714 --> 00:18:11.965
That's it.

00:18:12.549 --> 00:18:14.384
Then I'll beat those two up

00:18:14.468 --> 00:18:17.012
And join our old boss Yong-man.

00:18:17.096 --> 00:18:18.097
Sit down.

00:18:20.182 --> 00:18:21.934
Just take care of your health.

00:18:22.976 --> 00:18:26.939
Your apartment complex is electing building representatives right now,

00:18:27.022 --> 00:18:30.776
And if you become one, you qualify to run for president.

00:18:31.693 --> 00:18:34.238
Doesn't this seem like fate, Mr. Park?

00:18:35.322 --> 00:18:37.282
You pocketed four billion over five years, right?

00:18:37.366 --> 00:18:39.535
-Yes. -But we don't have that much time.

00:18:39.618 --> 00:18:40.828
We only have three months.

00:18:40.911 --> 00:18:43.038
Don't worry about that.

00:18:43.122 --> 00:18:46.250
If you become the president, you'll get the official seal.

00:18:46.333 --> 00:18:48.836
To execute payments, you need the president's and the manager's seal.

00:18:48.919 --> 00:18:52.923
With those, you can just stamp it, withdraw the cash and flee abroad.

00:18:53.006 --> 00:18:53.882
That's it.

00:18:54.550 --> 00:18:56.385
So we'd just need the manager's seal.

00:18:56.468 --> 00:18:57.719
That's what I'm telling you.

00:18:57.803 --> 00:19:00.097
Then how would we acquire that?

00:19:00.180 --> 00:19:01.098
Come on!

00:19:01.181 --> 00:19:02.891
You guys are big and strong.

00:19:02.975 --> 00:19:05.102
It'll be easy to get your hands on one seal.

00:19:05.185 --> 00:19:07.521
You can hang him off the rooftop like you did to me

00:19:07.604 --> 00:19:09.398
Or coax him into splitting it with you.

00:19:09.481 --> 00:19:11.441
You can decide on that later.

00:19:11.525 --> 00:19:13.360
But first, Mr. Park,

00:19:13.443 --> 00:19:15.112
You have to run for building rep.

00:19:16.864 --> 00:19:19.575
The 17,857,420,000 won

00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:23.203
Along with the money we have would be 21,357,420,000 won.

00:19:25.038 --> 00:19:25.956
That would be enough

00:19:26.582 --> 00:19:27.875
To protect Yong-man

00:19:27.958 --> 00:19:31.753
And help Gyeong-nam, Je-gil, and Big Guy achieve their dreams.

00:19:32.421 --> 00:19:34.339
I have to pull this off,

00:19:34.423 --> 00:19:35.507
No matter what.

00:19:36.216 --> 00:19:38.844
SEOUL JUNGBU DETENTION CENTER

00:19:41.471 --> 00:19:44.683
Hey, why are you visiting so often?

00:19:44.766 --> 00:19:47.019
Why do you look so awful? Let me see.

00:19:47.644 --> 00:19:49.646
Are there guys bullying you in there?

00:19:49.730 --> 00:19:51.773
Of course not.

00:19:51.857 --> 00:19:53.734
They treat me with respect

00:19:53.817 --> 00:19:57.654
Since I was the former boss of the Oasis Gang.

00:19:57.738 --> 00:20:01.241
They let me use the bathroom first in the morning

00:20:01.325 --> 00:20:03.327
And give me the most meat during our meals.

00:20:03.410 --> 00:20:05.996
Should I keep going?

00:20:10.375 --> 00:20:11.877
I just feel sorry, that's all.

00:20:12.628 --> 00:20:13.879
Just hang in there.

00:20:13.962 --> 00:20:15.839
I found a way to get you out.

00:20:16.548 --> 00:20:19.676
Don't do anything bad because of me, Hae-kang.

00:20:20.302 --> 00:20:21.470
It's nothing bad.

00:20:21.553 --> 00:20:23.347
Then what is it?

00:20:26.099 --> 00:20:27.935
Nobody's getting harmed,

00:20:28.018 --> 00:20:29.353
So it's nothing bad.

00:20:29.436 --> 00:20:30.771
Park Hae-kang.

00:20:30.854 --> 00:20:32.314
You told me to focus on my life.

00:20:35.108 --> 00:20:37.402
I need you in my life.

00:20:37.486 --> 00:20:39.029
I need you, so

00:20:40.072 --> 00:20:41.823
Just get ready to leave.

00:21:00.634 --> 00:21:02.219
DAILY REPAYMENT, SAME-DAY LOAN

00:21:07.432 --> 00:21:09.768
5-MINUTE LOAN NO COLLATERAL OR GUARANTOR REQUIRED

00:21:09.851 --> 00:21:11.061
Hey, Hae-kang.

00:21:11.144 --> 00:21:12.813
-Go on in. -Hurry.

00:21:17.025 --> 00:21:20.279
I heard you took Dongseong Temple's donation box.

00:21:20.362 --> 00:21:23.699
The head monk owes over 50 million won.

00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:28.662
Why would you do something I didn't even tell you to do?

00:21:29.997 --> 00:21:31.498
You'll hurt yourself, you idiot.

00:21:33.959 --> 00:21:35.168
Take it easy, okay?

00:21:36.336 --> 00:21:37.212
Yes, Boss.

00:21:47.556 --> 00:21:49.182
LOAN AGREEMENT

00:22:02.863 --> 00:22:04.489
I heard your father died.

00:22:06.783 --> 00:22:12.456
I've been keeping this in case he asked for you again

00:22:13.415 --> 00:22:15.083
But I don't need it now.

00:22:23.675 --> 00:22:24.760
You can leave.

00:22:25.677 --> 00:22:27.095
Don't do anything dangerous

00:22:27.846 --> 00:22:29.639
And just do what you want.

00:22:31.558 --> 00:22:34.770
It's the end for us now.

00:22:48.283 --> 00:22:49.284
I

00:22:49.367 --> 00:22:51.036
I want to stay here.

00:22:51.787 --> 00:22:54.164
With you, Boss.

00:23:16.186 --> 00:23:17.104
What's going on?

00:23:17.854 --> 00:23:19.481
I don't know. Was there an accident?

00:23:19.564 --> 00:23:21.024
Why aren't you moving your car? Hey!

00:23:21.108 --> 00:23:23.693
-Just a moment. -Hurry up!

00:23:23.777 --> 00:23:25.028
Of course. Please wait.

00:23:25.112 --> 00:23:28.156
Sir, why don't we talk after you move your car first?

00:23:28.240 --> 00:23:30.033
-Don't you see this? -No.

00:23:30.117 --> 00:23:31.118
Why should I?

00:23:31.201 --> 00:23:33.370
Sir, you're causing inconvenience for the residents

00:23:33.453 --> 00:23:34.621
By blocking the parking lot.

00:23:34.704 --> 00:23:35.914
What about me?

00:23:36.498 --> 00:23:37.666
What about my inconvenience?

00:23:37.749 --> 00:23:39.543
I'm a resident here too!

00:23:40.127 --> 00:23:41.878
So why the hell did you stick

00:23:41.962 --> 00:23:44.881
-this parking violation notice on my car? -Record this.

00:23:44.965 --> 00:23:46.633
Do you know how much this car costs?

00:23:46.716 --> 00:23:51.388
Sir, that was because you kept parking across two or three spaces

00:23:51.471 --> 00:23:53.807
-Yun-seo -Right?

00:23:54.307 --> 00:23:58.103
We kept getting complaints, so we had no choice.

00:23:58.186 --> 00:24:01.690
I live here. I pay the maintenance fees and park where I want.

00:24:01.773 --> 00:24:04.901
What does it matter to you if I take two or three spaces?

00:24:04.985 --> 00:24:07.904
I'm replacing my windshield, so bring me ten million for that.

00:24:07.988 --> 00:24:09.281
Sir!

00:24:09.364 --> 00:24:12.576
You've been parking terribly over and over again!

00:24:12.659 --> 00:24:15.287
If you don't move your car, we're reporting this.

00:24:15.370 --> 00:24:16.830
-I'm calling the cops! -The cops?

00:24:16.913 --> 00:24:18.373
-What are you doing? -Calm down.

00:24:18.456 --> 00:24:20.917
Lady, you think calling the cops will change anything?

00:24:21.001 --> 00:24:22.377
This isn't a public road,

00:24:22.460 --> 00:24:24.880
So the police can't tow my car.

00:24:24.963 --> 00:24:26.840
Don't act so bold if you're ignorant!

00:24:26.923 --> 00:24:28.758
How dare you call me ignorant?

00:24:28.842 --> 00:24:30.051
You're the one who's ignorant!

00:24:34.973 --> 00:24:37.100
Move!

00:24:47.194 --> 00:24:49.446
Oh, my gosh. Are they crazy?

00:24:49.529 --> 00:24:50.822
Nice. How satisfying.

00:24:57.746 --> 00:25:00.540
Wait Wait!

00:25:01.249 --> 00:25:02.250
What?

00:25:02.918 --> 00:25:04.044
What's wrong with you?

00:25:04.127 --> 00:25:05.337
Have you lost your mind?

00:25:05.420 --> 00:25:06.546
How

00:25:08.882 --> 00:25:12.636
How can you just ram into someone else's car like this?

00:25:12.719 --> 00:25:15.347
You seemed to be unable to move your car, so I did it for you.

00:25:15.430 --> 00:25:17.015
Don't be ridiculous.

00:25:17.098 --> 00:25:19.017
Do you know how much this costs?

00:25:19.100 --> 00:25:20.936
It's 300 million won!

00:25:21.019 --> 00:25:23.063
-Were you prepared for that? -It's 300 million.

00:25:23.146 --> 00:25:25.941
He's going to have to pay 300 million for his temper.

00:25:26.024 --> 00:25:28.193
I have no money to give to someone like you.

00:25:28.777 --> 00:25:30.904
You can sue me or report me. Whatever you like.

00:25:30.987 --> 00:25:33.573
Would the police even do anything?

00:25:33.657 --> 00:25:35.492
Okay, fine.

00:25:36.284 --> 00:25:39.079
Nobody's entering the parking lot today!

00:25:41.873 --> 00:25:44.125
Don't do this. Come on.

00:25:54.177 --> 00:25:55.220
CHUNG-WON

00:25:55.303 --> 00:25:56.304
All right.

00:26:00.809 --> 00:26:02.143
I'm sorry.

00:26:02.227 --> 00:26:05.480
I scratched your car, so I'll compensate you for it.

00:26:05.563 --> 00:26:09.025
Why is this apartment complex filled with psychos?

00:26:09.943 --> 00:26:12.654
This car is really expensive. Are you loaded?

00:26:15.073 --> 00:26:17.325
It looks like a budget model from about ten years ago.

00:26:17.409 --> 00:26:21.121
Looking at its condition, it seems like you got it used for about 80 million.

00:26:21.204 --> 00:26:23.957
Of course, I'll compensate you for it.

00:26:25.250 --> 00:26:27.043
The thing about a car

00:26:27.127 --> 00:26:29.879
Is that once it's been repaired, it depreciates massively.

00:26:29.963 --> 00:26:31.673
I'll cover everything.

00:26:31.756 --> 00:26:33.049
Mr. Kim,

00:26:33.133 --> 00:26:36.845
Compensate him in full so he won't feel upset.

00:26:36.928 --> 00:26:38.013
Yes, sir.

00:26:38.513 --> 00:26:40.181
But I'm a businessman,

00:26:40.265 --> 00:26:43.560
So I only feel satisfied when calculations are precise.

00:26:43.643 --> 00:26:46.604
You wasted my precious evening

00:26:46.688 --> 00:26:49.232
And the time of all the residents here,

00:26:49.316 --> 00:26:50.817
Caused a disturbance,

00:26:50.900 --> 00:26:54.529
And interfered with the management office's work,

00:26:54.612 --> 00:26:57.157
So I'm planning on suing you for that.

00:26:57.240 --> 00:26:58.074
What do you say?

00:26:58.658 --> 00:27:01.119
I have about 12 lawyers in my company.

00:27:01.202 --> 00:27:02.912
Do you think you can handle that?

00:27:06.082 --> 00:27:07.292
I'm going to sue you too.

00:27:07.375 --> 00:27:08.752
You should.

00:27:08.835 --> 00:27:11.212
Our lawyers are excellent at their job.

00:27:11.296 --> 00:27:12.964
They're good at digging up dirt,

00:27:13.048 --> 00:27:14.174
Picking people apart,

00:27:14.257 --> 00:27:17.427
And completely destroying their lives.

00:27:17.510 --> 00:27:18.803
That's their specialty.

00:27:18.887 --> 00:27:22.182
All within legal boundaries, of course.

00:27:24.225 --> 00:27:26.811
So can you move your car now?

00:27:31.441 --> 00:27:33.777
-Where is he going? -Is he running away?

00:27:34.861 --> 00:27:37.530
He's the guy living in the penthouse in Building 123, isn't he?

00:27:37.614 --> 00:27:39.991
He's so cool.

00:27:40.075 --> 00:27:41.701
Isn't he so cool?

00:27:42.535 --> 00:27:44.287
He really is cool.

00:27:44.371 --> 00:27:46.915
I was the one who damaged the car in the end,

00:27:46.998 --> 00:27:48.917
So my secretary will take care of everything.

00:27:49.417 --> 00:27:51.378
We'll handle the repair costs for your car too.

00:27:51.461 --> 00:27:52.462
That's all right.

00:27:53.129 --> 00:27:54.214
I'll handle my own car.

00:27:54.297 --> 00:27:57.092
You dealt with the troublesome nuisance

00:27:57.175 --> 00:27:59.427
And helped save my time.

00:27:59.511 --> 00:28:02.180
It's only fair that I handle your repair costs as well.

00:28:05.100 --> 00:28:07.477
I'm Lee Chung-won from Building 123.

00:28:14.150 --> 00:28:16.111
I'm Park Hae-kang from Building 114.

00:28:19.864 --> 00:28:22.075
You're really cool, sir!

00:28:22.158 --> 00:28:23.910
Everyone, applause!

00:28:23.993 --> 00:28:24.994
You're so cool!

00:28:25.745 --> 00:28:26.830
You're amazing!

00:28:28.456 --> 00:28:29.541
He's so cool.

00:28:31.793 --> 00:28:34.546
I ended up having to kiss him!

00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:37.549
What? You did what?

00:28:37.632 --> 00:28:38.550
We

00:28:40.176 --> 00:28:41.094
We kissed.

00:28:42.137 --> 00:28:43.346
For real?

00:28:43.430 --> 00:28:46.891
Still, if it weren't for him, you would've been short on money.

00:28:46.975 --> 00:28:48.518
But what about this month?

00:28:50.270 --> 00:28:51.396
I don't know.

00:28:51.479 --> 00:28:52.564
Here, take this.

00:28:53.732 --> 00:28:54.774
Seriously?

00:28:54.858 --> 00:28:57.026
You're delivering milk to earn that money?

00:28:57.110 --> 00:28:58.403
You look so exhausted.

00:29:01.656 --> 00:29:02.741
It's 3000 won.

00:29:03.491 --> 00:29:04.492
What's 3000 won?

00:29:04.576 --> 00:29:06.411
That probiotic drink you're drinking.

00:29:09.956 --> 00:29:13.168
I have to buy it? Fine, I will.

00:29:13.251 --> 00:29:15.587
And I'll pay for dinner as well.

00:29:15.670 --> 00:29:17.213
Forget dinner.

00:29:17.297 --> 00:29:19.382
Can't you just buy all of these while you're at it?

00:29:22.135 --> 00:29:24.012
No, this is crazy.

00:29:24.095 --> 00:29:26.431
Just go and talk to your sister.

00:29:26.514 --> 00:29:29.225
Tell her the truth and just ask her for help one more time.

00:29:30.059 --> 00:29:31.144
This is insane.

00:29:31.227 --> 00:29:33.313
I know, but,

00:29:33.396 --> 00:29:36.191
I can't bear to see the disappointment on her face.

00:29:36.274 --> 00:29:39.277
And how can I do that to her when she helped me for ten years?

00:29:39.360 --> 00:29:41.404
She should focus on her own life now.

00:29:46.910 --> 00:29:48.119
Then,

00:29:48.203 --> 00:29:50.580
How about this?

00:29:50.663 --> 00:29:53.208
Just do this until the end of my term.

00:29:53.291 --> 00:29:54.501
That's fine, isn't it?

00:30:08.973 --> 00:30:09.808
Hey, Ha-jeong.

00:30:11.059 --> 00:30:12.560
Were you waiting for me?

00:30:21.694 --> 00:30:26.074
I treated my colleagues to dinner today

00:30:26.157 --> 00:30:27.951
To celebrate my sister becoming a lawyer.

00:30:28.910 --> 00:30:30.411
Why would you treat them?

00:30:31.371 --> 00:30:33.456
Hey, I've been working there for six years,

00:30:33.540 --> 00:30:35.750
But I never treated them to anything.

00:30:36.334 --> 00:30:39.587
And I never joined them for dinner unless it was a company gathering.

00:30:39.671 --> 00:30:42.131
You know I'm not a morning person.

00:30:42.215 --> 00:30:44.175
But I woke up early

00:30:44.259 --> 00:30:47.804
Every day for six years to pack lunch so I could save money.

00:30:47.887 --> 00:30:49.013
Six years.

00:30:50.265 --> 00:30:52.475
I know.

00:30:53.434 --> 00:30:55.728
I'm not that smart,

00:30:55.812 --> 00:30:58.690
But I've been working really hard to support you.

00:30:59.566 --> 00:31:00.900
I know that.

00:31:01.401 --> 00:31:03.695
But why are you saying this?

00:31:03.778 --> 00:31:05.864
You're starting to scare me.

00:31:08.324 --> 00:31:09.367
Ha-ri.

00:31:12.161 --> 00:31:14.873
Can it be my turn now?

00:31:14.956 --> 00:31:16.749
It's time for you to help me.

00:31:17.917 --> 00:31:20.962
You know my dream was to be a patissier.

00:31:21.588 --> 00:31:23.590
I want to try that again.

00:31:24.924 --> 00:31:26.968
Before it's too late

00:31:27.051 --> 00:31:29.137
And before I get any worse,

00:31:29.220 --> 00:31:31.055
I want a new start.

00:31:31.681 --> 00:31:32.891
What do you mean, "worse"?

00:31:33.641 --> 00:31:36.686
You're not treating people badly like you do to me, are you?

00:31:37.270 --> 00:31:38.396
Of course not.

00:31:38.980 --> 00:31:40.732
Just forget that.

00:31:42.191 --> 00:31:43.651
But you'll help me, won't you?

00:31:44.652 --> 00:31:45.486
This is it.

00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:47.697
If I miss this chance, I'll never be able to tell her.

00:31:47.780 --> 00:31:48.990
I should tell her the truth.

00:31:50.742 --> 00:31:51.618
Kang Ha-jeong.

