I was waiting for you, Miss Kang Ha-ri.

00:49:02.481 --> 00:49:03.940
How did you know my name?

00:49:04.024 --> 00:49:05.359
And my workplace?

00:49:05.442 --> 00:49:08.737
I had to meet you, so I asked around.

00:49:10.572 --> 00:49:13.283
Did you know that leaking personal data may be punishable

00:49:13.367 --> 00:49:17.245
By up to 5 years in prison or a fine of up to 50 million won?

00:49:17.329 --> 00:49:19.289
And if you've obtained personal information

00:49:19.373 --> 00:49:21.041
Through improper means

00:49:21.124 --> 00:49:24.211
Or used information learned in the course of your duties

00:49:24.294 --> 00:49:27.047
For other purposes, you may be subject to up to three years

00:49:27.756 --> 00:49:28.715
Keep going.

00:49:30.717 --> 00:49:31.718
Never mind.

00:49:32.719 --> 00:49:33.762
What did you want to say?

00:49:34.346 --> 00:49:35.681
Let's work on something together.

00:49:36.807 --> 00:49:37.849
Why would I do that?

00:49:38.767 --> 00:49:41.103
Play the role of my wife for three months.

00:49:42.187 --> 00:49:43.980
Play the role of what?

00:49:44.064 --> 00:49:45.315
My wife.

00:49:45.399 --> 00:49:48.193
Just think of it as another stand-in service gig.

00:49:48.276 --> 00:49:49.236
No.

00:49:49.820 --> 00:49:51.238
Aren't you in need of money?

00:49:51.321 --> 00:49:52.989
I'm always in need of money.

00:49:53.073 --> 00:49:54.908
Well, I need you and you need money.

00:49:54.991 --> 00:49:56.243
It'll be a win-win situation.

00:49:56.326 --> 00:49:57.703
I don't need your money.

00:49:57.786 --> 00:49:58.787
Why not?

00:49:58.870 --> 00:50:00.831
Because it's dirty money?

00:50:01.623 --> 00:50:03.709
I don't know why you need a wife,

00:50:03.792 --> 00:50:06.336
But I'm sure it's shady work with shady money.

00:50:07.212 --> 00:50:08.088
Let me ask one thing.

00:50:10.298 --> 00:50:11.967
Are you in a gang?

00:50:12.551 --> 00:50:15.679
It's pretty big, right? I saw all those guys at the wedding.

00:50:16.763 --> 00:50:18.098
Let me be clear.

00:50:18.181 --> 00:50:19.558
I've retired,

00:50:19.641 --> 00:50:22.519
But even after we retire, we attend important events for each other.

00:50:24.479 --> 00:50:26.773
-So you're not in a gang anymore. -What?

00:50:26.857 --> 00:50:28.066
Still, my answer is no.

00:50:28.150 --> 00:50:30.986
As someone working in law, I don't want to get involved with you.

00:50:32.487 --> 00:50:34.740
I believe you're no longer working in law.

00:50:37.576 --> 00:50:41.037
I'll excuse myself first. I hope we don't meet each other again.

00:50:41.121 --> 00:50:44.166
Do you care about background even when it comes to money?

00:50:44.249 --> 00:50:46.334
Money doesn't have a good or bad education,

00:50:46.418 --> 00:50:48.837
Or differences in social status or occupation.

00:50:48.920 --> 00:50:51.673
Money is just money. Why would you refuse?

00:50:56.928 --> 00:50:58.054
A hundred million.

00:50:59.806 --> 00:51:01.391
A hundred million for three months.

00:51:03.685 --> 00:51:06.271
I'll give you 30 million as a down payment right away.

00:51:08.356 --> 00:51:09.566
Did he say 30 million?

00:51:09.649 --> 00:51:11.818
With that, I could help Ha-jeong

00:51:11.902 --> 00:51:14.154
And not have to worry about money for a while.

00:51:14.237 --> 00:51:16.907
Are you mad? What the hell are you thinking?

00:51:16.990 --> 00:51:18.408
You want to accept his money?

00:51:19.034 --> 00:51:20.619
Get a grip!

00:51:26.792 --> 00:51:27.793
Deal.

00:51:27.876 --> 00:51:29.085
I CAN DO IT!

00:51:29.169 --> 00:51:30.462
Whatever.

00:51:34.049 --> 00:51:35.801
KANG HA-RI'S BANK ACCOUNT 30,098,607 WON

00:51:36.843 --> 00:51:38.261
It's only three months.

00:51:39.012 --> 00:51:41.723
Just think of it as a long-term stand-in service gig.

00:51:41.807 --> 00:51:42.974
You can do it, Kang Ha-ri!

00:51:43.058 --> 00:51:44.059
Let's do this!

00:51:47.813 --> 00:51:50.607
Sir, did she really

00:51:51.316 --> 00:51:53.151
Say "deal" and agree to it?

00:51:53.235 --> 00:51:54.861
She'll do anything for money.

00:51:55.612 --> 00:51:56.738
It makes things easier.

00:51:56.822 --> 00:51:58.865
So we got a wife.

00:51:59.449 --> 00:52:01.618
You're keeping an eye on the Lizard, right?

00:52:02.869 --> 00:52:03.703
Yes.

00:52:07.666 --> 00:52:09.501
I was just doing some fortune reading.

00:52:09.584 --> 00:52:10.544
I'll stop.

00:52:13.088 --> 00:52:14.714
I'll clean this up. It's messy.

00:52:15.966 --> 00:52:17.217
My socks.

00:52:19.427 --> 00:52:21.346
What is it? Say something.

00:52:22.055 --> 00:52:23.473
Just tell me.

00:52:23.557 --> 00:52:25.225
Be my father.

00:52:26.768 --> 00:52:28.103
If you play the role of my father

00:52:28.186 --> 00:52:30.480
And cooperate until I become the president,

00:52:30.564 --> 00:52:33.275
I'll clear all your debt.

00:52:34.234 --> 00:52:35.819
You're a wanted man,

00:52:35.902 --> 00:52:37.612
So you have nowhere to go anyway.

00:52:39.364 --> 00:52:40.198
Deal.

00:52:43.785 --> 00:52:44.619
Wait.

00:52:46.204 --> 00:52:48.790
Do I get a bonus if we succeed?

00:52:50.292 --> 00:52:51.585
I'll let you live.

00:53:04.139 --> 00:53:06.850
I knew it was my lucky day today,

00:53:08.518 --> 00:53:10.020
Of course I miss you.

00:53:10.812 --> 00:53:13.565
So did you brush your teeth or not?

00:53:13.648 --> 00:53:14.649
Let me see.

00:53:16.109 --> 00:53:19.154
Make sure to brush your teeth well, or you'll get cavities.

00:53:21.114 --> 00:53:22.741
Hey, Gyeong-buk. It's Uncle Hae-kang.

00:53:22.824 --> 00:53:24.284
Uncle!

00:53:24.367 --> 00:53:27.329
You've gotten even more handsome, Gyeong-buk.

00:53:27.412 --> 00:53:29.039
You should greet him properly.

00:53:29.956 --> 00:53:32.125
I have to get back to work now,

00:53:32.208 --> 00:53:34.085
So listen to your grandma and go to bed.

00:53:34.169 --> 00:53:35.670
Goodnight, Dad.

00:53:38.715 --> 00:53:40.383
Gyeong-buk's grown so much.

00:53:41.593 --> 00:53:43.219
He seems to grow every day.

00:53:43.303 --> 00:53:44.721
You must miss him.

00:53:50.310 --> 00:53:52.062
Well, I have no other choice.

00:53:52.145 --> 00:53:53.438
Let's bring him here.

00:53:53.521 --> 00:53:54.606
What?

00:53:54.689 --> 00:53:58.193
Let's raise him as my son until our project's over.

00:54:00.904 --> 00:54:04.157
You said you wanted him to attend Stanford University.

00:54:04.240 --> 00:54:05.450
Then he should learn English.

00:54:06.034 --> 00:54:08.286
How long will you keep him stuck in the countryside?

00:54:08.370 --> 00:54:09.955
He can't learn any English there.

00:54:10.622 --> 00:54:12.248
This is a good opportunity for him.

00:54:12.332 --> 00:54:13.500
Let's send him

00:54:14.292 --> 00:54:15.460
To an English kindergarten.

00:54:15.543 --> 00:54:17.587
An English kindergarten?

00:54:25.720 --> 00:54:27.514
The preparations are complete.

00:54:28.098 --> 00:54:30.308
It's time to begin.

00:54:36.606 --> 00:54:39.025
FAMILY PHOTO SHOOT MODEL APPLICATIONS

00:54:48.284 --> 00:54:49.119
Sir

00:54:49.953 --> 00:54:51.037
I brought coffee.

00:54:51.121 --> 00:54:52.747
-Big Guy. -Right.

00:54:55.333 --> 00:54:56.751
Are you an artist or what?

00:54:57.252 --> 00:54:59.504
Don't be so rude.

00:55:00.338 --> 00:55:02.674
I'm going for a retired artist vibe.

00:55:03.591 --> 00:55:04.592
Don't I look cool?

00:55:04.676 --> 00:55:08.722
I was popular among the ladies when I was young.

00:55:09.264 --> 00:55:11.224
I'll win over the elderly women

00:55:11.307 --> 00:55:15.228
And help you secure the election.

00:55:19.691 --> 00:55:21.609
Superman!

00:55:21.693 --> 00:55:22.819
Uncle!

00:55:22.902 --> 00:55:24.362
Gyeong-buk!

00:55:25.947 --> 00:55:27.741
When did you get so big, kiddo?

00:55:28.366 --> 00:55:29.284
Uncle.

00:55:29.367 --> 00:55:31.870
I missed you so much.

00:55:32.412 --> 00:55:34.330
I missed you too, kiddo.

00:55:37.625 --> 00:55:39.836
He didn't even give his own dad a kiss.

00:55:39.919 --> 00:55:40.879
I feel upset.

00:55:40.962 --> 00:55:43.089
He was always so nice to Gyeong-buk.

00:55:43.173 --> 00:55:44.049
Gyeong-buk!

00:55:44.632 --> 00:55:45.592
Let me carry

00:55:45.675 --> 00:55:47.260
I can't now. You carry him.

00:55:47.343 --> 00:55:48.303
You're so cute.

00:55:48.928 --> 00:55:51.431
But Mr. Park's wife hasn't arrived yet.

00:55:53.683 --> 00:55:55.351
What if she doesn't turn up?

00:55:55.435 --> 00:55:57.312
She could've just taken the money.

00:55:57.395 --> 00:55:58.271
She'll come.

00:55:58.354 --> 00:55:59.647
I'm sure of it.

00:56:00.273 --> 00:56:02.650
She'll come for the remaining amount.

00:56:02.734 --> 00:56:04.319
It's already been ten minutes.

00:56:11.993 --> 00:56:13.661
It's a princess.

00:56:13.745 --> 00:56:14.829
Sorry I'm late.

00:56:15.413 --> 00:56:17.207
As you see, I had to put in some effort.

00:56:19.918 --> 00:56:21.377
How about a brief introduction?

00:56:21.461 --> 00:56:24.964
You met them at the wedding. My employees.

00:56:25.048 --> 00:56:25.965
Gyeong-buk, come here.

00:56:26.633 --> 00:56:28.551
This is our son, Gyeong-buk.

00:56:29.469 --> 00:56:31.262
I have a son?

00:56:32.806 --> 00:56:34.349
You never mentioned that.

00:56:34.432 --> 00:56:36.017
I'm introducing him to you now.

00:56:37.060 --> 00:56:38.645
You're so pretty.

00:56:38.728 --> 00:56:40.897
Uncle, I like her.

00:56:42.649 --> 00:56:44.901
Nice to meet you. I'm Gyeong-buk.

00:56:47.487 --> 00:56:48.613
Nice to meet you.

00:56:52.283 --> 00:56:53.201
And this

00:56:53.952 --> 00:56:56.412
I'm your father-in-law.

00:56:56.996 --> 00:56:59.666
Since everyone's gathered now, let's take the photo.

00:57:00.166 --> 00:57:02.418
Bonjour, charming lady.

00:57:12.095 --> 00:57:13.638
Is everyone ready?

00:57:13.721 --> 00:57:14.722
-Yes. -Yes.

00:57:16.266 --> 00:57:17.851
You're a family, aren't you?

00:57:18.351 --> 00:57:19.435
-Yes. -Yes.

00:57:19.519 --> 00:57:21.187
Your configuration is a bit awkward.

00:57:23.314 --> 00:57:24.983
-Okay. -I can move.

00:57:25.066 --> 00:57:26.609
Let's go with option two, then.

00:57:27.610 --> 00:57:29.529
I'll sit on this side.

00:57:31.906 --> 00:57:35.118
If it's your first family photo, you might feel a bit awkward.

00:57:35.201 --> 00:57:38.496
You're leaving a lasting memory, so let me help place you.

00:57:38.580 --> 00:57:39.914
-The grandfather? -Yes?

00:57:39.998 --> 00:57:41.416
Please sit in the armchair.

00:57:41.499 --> 00:57:42.792
-Here? -Yes.

00:57:42.876 --> 00:57:44.752
Right. I did think it was weird.

00:57:44.836 --> 00:57:45.670
Move.

00:57:46.713 --> 00:57:49.174
He told me to sit here.

00:57:51.092 --> 00:57:53.052
And the father and mother.

00:57:53.136 --> 00:57:54.220
Sit on the loveseat.

00:57:54.304 --> 00:57:56.014
The father can sit in the middle.

00:57:56.723 --> 00:57:58.057
Oh, I'm the mother.

00:58:00.018 --> 00:58:01.060
And our little prince.

00:58:01.144 --> 00:58:03.062
Why don't you sit on your dad's lap?

00:58:11.696 --> 00:58:14.407
My nephew, you should sit with your dad.

00:58:14.491 --> 00:58:15.992
He loves his uncle.

00:58:16.493 --> 00:58:17.327
Right.

00:58:17.911 --> 00:58:19.454
And the others, stand in the back.

00:58:19.537 --> 00:58:21.998
All right. One, two, three.

00:58:26.878 --> 00:58:28.379
One last time, everyone.

00:58:28.463 --> 00:58:31.549
One, two, smile!

00:58:34.219 --> 00:58:35.136
I'm going to win.

00:58:35.220 --> 00:58:36.971
I'll win no matter what.

00:58:37.764 --> 00:58:41.976
I'll win and save Yong-man and protect my guys.

00:58:42.060 --> 00:58:43.102
I'll make sure of it.

00:59:23.101 --> 00:59:24.936
Dad! Mom!

00:59:25.019 --> 00:59:26.479
Grandpa! Uncle!

00:59:26.563 --> 00:59:28.273
Hurry up!

00:59:36.531 --> 00:59:38.449
THE APARTMENT JOB

01:00:02.557 --> 01:00:03.516
I'm Park Hae-kang.

01:00:03.600 --> 01:00:04.601
I'm Jang Suk-jin.

01:00:04.684 --> 01:00:06.394
You're quite handsome.

01:00:06.477 --> 01:00:09.355
Was having three candidates part of your perfect plan?

01:00:09.439 --> 01:00:10.732
What do you think, Mr. Kim?

01:00:10.815 --> 01:00:14.569
Do you think Park Hae-kang can be a diligent worker for True Value?

01:00:14.652 --> 01:00:17.196
"I'll be a diligent worker for True Value."

01:00:17.280 --> 01:00:18.823
How exactly do you plan on doing that?

01:00:18.906 --> 01:00:20.908
-I'll take care of this problem! -Win-win!

01:00:20.992 --> 01:00:22.994
Deliveries will be sorted by building

01:00:23.077 --> 01:00:25.455
And handed over directly after verifying the recipient.

01:00:25.538 --> 01:00:26.372
Delivery!

01:00:26.456 --> 01:00:28.666
Everyone can just take their own packages home.

01:00:28.750 --> 01:00:30.251
How long will they keep this up?

01:00:30.335 --> 01:00:32.670
"Request to discontinue the delivery service"?

01:00:32.754 --> 01:00:34.631
The proof of delivery photos look fine.

01:00:34.714 --> 01:00:36.924
Boss, this is Candidate Jang's place.

01:00:37.008 --> 01:00:38.676
She's going negative over a building rep election?

01:00:38.760 --> 01:00:40.511
Let's take down

01:00:40.595 --> 01:00:41.721
Jang Suk-jin.

01:00:44.891 --> 01:00:46.893
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park

